            <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">A page layout is used for page specifications (e.g., size, margins) and to apply certain content (e.g., headers, footers, page numbers) to many (or all) topics in print-based output. </MadCap:conditionalText>
            <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">A <a href="../../../../../Flare/Page-Layouts/Page-Layouts.htm" MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only" MadCap:excludeAction="unbind">page layout</a> is used for page specifications (e.g., size, margins) and to apply certain content (e.g., headers, footers, page numbers) to many (or all) topics in print-based output. </MadCap:conditionalText>It allows for easy configuration through the use of content frames, bleeds, crop marks, registration marks, margins, padding, alignment features, and more.</p>
